\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The revised paper is titled 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Exploring Asymmetries in the Effects of El Ni単o-Southern Oscillation on
 U.S.
 Food and Agricultural Stock Returns
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 State-dependent local projection (Jorda, 2005) methods have become the
 state-of-the-art technique for investigating asymmetric or nonlinear responses
 to economic (and other) shocks.
 We apply this methodology to examine whether El Ni単o-Southern Oscillation
 (ENSO) has asymmetric impacts on U.S.
 food and agricultural stock returns.
 Using weekly data from 1990:01 to 2019:04, we find support for the hypothesis
 that food and agricultural stock returns respond asymmetrically to ENSO
 shocks.
 In particular, we provide evidence that El Ni単o shocks typically decrease
 or have no effects on U.S.
 food and agricultural stock returns, whereas La Ni単a shocks generally increase
 returns.
 The analysis, thus, emphasizes the need to consider asymmetries in the
 impacts of ENSO, as failure to do so might result in misleading conclusions
 about the effect of ENSO on U.S.
 food and agricultural stock returns.
\end_layout

